
[1]incoherency

   INCOHE'RENCY, n. [in and coherence.]

   1. Want of coherence; want of cohesion or adherence; looseness or
   unconnected state of parts, as of a powder.

   2. Want of connection; incongruity; inconsistency; want of agreement,
   or dependence of one part on another; as the incoherence of arguments,
   facts or principles.

   3. Inconsistency; that which does not agree with other parts of the
   same thing.
